sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / kubectl
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Webhook as Admission Webhooks<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Operator as ModelRegistry Controller<br/>(controller-runtime)
    participant MigMgr as Storage Migration Manager
    participant OAuthProxy as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant REST as REST Container<br/>(model-registry)<br/>{rest.port}/TCP HTTP
    participant gRPC as gRPC Container<br/>(mlmd-grpc-server)<br/>{grpc.port}/TCP
    participant DB as PostgreSQL / MySQL<br/>{db.port}/TCP

    Note over User,DB: Flow 1: ModelRegistry Instance Reconciliation

    User->>K8sAPI: Create/Update ModelRegistry CR
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate (defaults images, ports, OAuth)
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated CR
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate (check DB config, namespace)
    Webhook->>K8sAPI: GET ModelRegistries (name uniqueness check)
    K8sAPI-->>Webhook: Existing registries
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admitted / Rejected

    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event (ModelRegistry changed)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update Deployment<br/>(REST + gRPC + OAuth proxy containers)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update Service, ServiceAccount,<br/>Role, RoleBinding, Group
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update Route (OpenShift)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update NetworkPolicy,<br/>OAuth secrets
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Resources reconciled

    Note over User,DB: Flow 2: Client Request (with OAuth)

    User->>OAuthProxy: HTTPS request via Route<br/>(TLS reencrypt, Bearer/OAuth token)
    OAuthProxy->>K8sAPI: TokenReview + SubjectAccessReview
    K8sAPI-->>OAuthProxy: Auth result
    OAuthProxy->>REST: Forward to localhost<br/>HTTP {rest.port}
    REST->>gRPC: gRPC call (localhost, same pod)<br/>{grpc.port}
    gRPC->>DB: Query metadata<br/>{db.port} (optional TLS)
    DB-->>gRPC: Query result
    gRPC-->>REST: gRPC response
    REST-->>OAuthProxy: HTTP response
    OAuthProxy-->>User: HTTPS response

    Note over MigMgr,K8sAPI: Flow 3: Storage Version Migration

    MigMgr->>K8sAPI: Check CRD storedVersions<br/>(v1alpha1 still present?)
    K8sAPI-->>MigMgr: storedVersions list
    alt SVM API available
        MigMgr->>K8sAPI: Create StorageVersionMigration CR
        K8sAPI-->>MigMgr: Migration status
    else SVM API not available (fallback)
        MigMgr->>K8sAPI: List all ModelRegistries (v1beta1)
        K8sAPI-->>MigMgr: ModelRegistry list
        MigMgr->>K8sAPI: Update each (triggers conversion webhook)
        K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /convert (v1alpha1 → v1beta1)
        Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Converted CR
    end

    Note over Operator,DB: Flow 4: Status Reconciliation (Pod Log Scraping)

    Operator->>K8sAPI: GET pods/log (gRPC + REST containers)
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Recent log lines
    Operator->>Operator: Regex match for DB errors,<br/>schema migration failures
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update ModelRegistry status conditions
